{"lemma":"ضَحْكُ","slug":"ضَحْكُ","root":"ض.ح.ك","root_slug":"ض-ح-ك","root_link":"/words/roots/ض-ح-ك","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n25591","n25595"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B6%D9%8E%D8%AD%D9%92%D9%83%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of ضَحِكَ (ḍaḥika) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"laughter"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to laugh","examples":[{"text":"الطِّفْلُ يَضْحَكُ بِصَوْتٍ عَالٍ عِنْدَمَا يَلْعَبُ مَعَ أَصْدِقَائِهِ","english":"The child laughs loudly when playing with his friends."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to jeer, to scoff"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make (someone) laugh"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ض ح ك (ḍ ḥ k). Compare Hebrew צָחַק (ṣāḥaq, “to laugh”)."},"ipa":["/dˤa.ħik/","/dˤiħk/","/dˤaħk/","/dˤa.ħi.ka/","/dˤaħ.ħa.ka/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n25591","headword_ar":"ضَحِكَ","root":"DHk","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, MA, O, Msb, K, &c.,) and some say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DiHikotu","text_ar":"ضِحِكْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"D","text_ar":"ض"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA, as from the K, [but not in the CK nor in my MS. copy of the K,]) to agree with the vowel of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"H","text_ar":"ح"},{"kind":"text","text":"because the latter is a faucial letter, and this is a correct dial. var. of which similar instances are mentioned, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaHaka","text_ar":"ضَحَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also is said to be a well known dial. var. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaHika","text_ar":"ضَحِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S. O,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaHikN","text_ar":"ضَحِكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DiHokN","text_ar":"ضِحْكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, MA, O, Msb, K, KL) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaHokN","text_ar":"ضَحْكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, MA, O, K, KL,) the first of which is the superior form, (IDrd, O,) [the second and third being contractions thereof,] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DiHikN","text_ar":"ضِحِكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K, KL,) and if you said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaHakN","text_ar":"ضَحَكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"it would be agreeable with analogy, (Az, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He laughed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA, KL, PS, TK;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bakaY","text_ar":"بَكَى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TK:) [see also 6:]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlD~aHiku","text_ar":"الضَّحِكُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is well known, as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the expanding of the face, and displaying of the teeth, by reason of happiness, joy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gladness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~abas~umu","text_ar":"التَّبَسُّمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the beginning thereof: thus in the Towsheeh and other works: (MF, TA:) and in like manner in the Mufradát [of Er-Rághib]; in which it is added that it is also used as meaning simply"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the being happy, joyful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"glad:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and sometimes as meaning simply"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the wondering"},{"kind":"text","text":"[at a thing]; and this is the meaning intended by him who says that it is peculiar to man: (TA:) [i. e.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaHika","text_ar":"ضَحِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", said of a man, signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he wondered;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eajiba","text_ar":"عَجِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O, K, TA;) with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino","text_ar":"مِنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"preposed to the object of wonder: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was frightened;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he feared."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaHika minohu","text_ar":"ضَحِكَ مِنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihi","text_ar":"بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", both meaning the same, (S, O, Msb,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He laughed at him; derided him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ridiculed him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he wondered at him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaHika A_ilayohi","text_ar":"ضَحِكَ اـِلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He behaved laughingly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cheerfully, towards him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (IDrd and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b$","text_ar":"بش"},{"kind":"text","text":"[See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba$~a lahu","text_ar":"بَشَّ لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b2-  Said of an ape,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He uttered a cry"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cries:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or one says of the ape when he utters a cry or cries,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaDoHaku","text_ar":"يَضْحَكُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TA,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he displays his teeth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grins."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaHika Als~aHaAbu","text_ar":"ضَحِكَ السَّحَابُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The clouds lightened."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA.) Hence the usage of the verb in a trad. cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHad~ava","text_ar":"تَحَدَّثَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O, TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaHika Algadiyru","text_ar":"ضَحِكَ الغَدِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The pool of water left by a torrent"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"glistened by reason of its fulness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-  [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaHika vagoruhu","text_ar":"ضَحِكَ ثَغْرُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His front teeth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his teeth, glistened"},{"kind":"text","text":"by reason of his laughing; meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he laughed so as to show his front teeth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his teeth."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b6-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaHika Alz~ahoru","text_ar":"ضَحِكَ الزَّهْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The flowers"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"looked gay,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"were as though they were laughing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaHikati AlA^aroDu","text_ar":"ضَحِكَتِ الاَرْضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The earth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"land, put forth its plants,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage, and its flowers."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaHikati Alr~iyaADu Eani AlA^azohaAri","text_ar":"ضَحِكَتِ الرِّيَاضُ عَنِ الاَزْهَارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The meadows,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gardens, displayed the flowers."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b7-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaHikati Aln~axolapu","text_ar":"ضَحِكَتِ النَّخْلَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The palm-tree put forth"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disclosed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaHok","text_ar":"ضَحْك"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aDoHakat","text_ar":"اَضْحَكَت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) [i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the spathe of the palm-tree,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Skr, O, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that covered the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloE","text_ar":"طَلْع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spadix"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"burst open."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Skr, O, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaHika AlT~aloEu","text_ar":"ضَحِكَ الطَّلْعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TlE","text_ar":"طلع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[here app. meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spathe of the palm-tree"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"split,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clave, open;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabas~ama","text_ar":"تَبَسَّمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b8-  And, as some assert, (ISd, TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaHikato","text_ar":"ضَحِكَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She menstruated;"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a hare; (ISd, Z, O, Msb, TA;) accord. to some, from the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaH~aAk","text_ar":"ضَحَّاك"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning the interior] of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloEap","text_ar":"طَلْعَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of the palm-tree] when it bursts open; (ISd, TA;) and hence, (K, TA,) said also in this sense of a woman, (O, Msb, K, TA,) accord. to Mujáhid, (O, TA,) and some others, (TA,) in the Kur xi. 74, (O, K, TA,) where some read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDaHakato","text_ar":"فَضَحَكَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is said to be a well-known dial. var.; (TA;) and likewise, accord. to some, said in this sense of the hyena, (O, TA,) when she sees blood, or as IAar says, when she eats the flesh of men and drinks their blood: (TA:) [it is commonly asserted by the Arabs that] the hare menstruates like women: (Kzw:) but with respect to this meaning as assigned to the verb in the Kur xi. 74, Fr says that he had not heard it from any person deserving of confidence; (O, TA; *) and Zj says that it is nought: both say that the meaning there is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she laughed by reason of happiness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and some say that there is an inversion in this case, what is meant being"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faba$~aronaAhaA biA_isoH`qa","text_ar":"فَبَشَّرْنَاهَا بِاـِسْحٰقَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDaHikato","text_ar":"فَضَحِكَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Fr, O, TA:) or the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she wondered;"},{"kind":"text","text":"so says I'Ab; and so Er-Rághib, who adds that it is confirmed by her saying, “ shall I bring forth a child when I am an old woman, and this my husband is an old man? verily this is indeed a wonderful thing: ” and that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faHaADato","text_ar":"فَحَاضَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is inserted by some of the expositors after"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDaHikato","text_ar":"فَضَحِكَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not an explanation of this expression, as some of them have imagined it to be, but is the mention of [a fact which was] a sign that the announcement was not that of an event improbable: or the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she was frightened;"},{"kind":"text","text":"so says Fr.: (TA:) and with respect to the meaning of this verb when said of the hyena, mentioned above, it is rejected by AHát and others: (TA:) IDrd says, on the authority of AHát, respecting the following verse of TaäbbataSharrà,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"taDoHaku AlD~aboEu liqatolaY hu*ayolK\n                      \n                     \n                        wataraY Al*~iy^oba lahaA yasotahil~u"},{"kind":"text","text":"that the meaning is (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The hyena displays her teeth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grins, on account of the slain"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of Hudheyl"},{"kind":"text","text":"], when she sees them, like as they say of the ass when he plucks out the [plant called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sil~iyaAnap","text_ar":"صِلِّيَانَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O, TA;) or, as others say, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the hyena snarls, displaying her teeth; and sees the wolf raising his voice in calling"},{"kind":"text","text":"the [other] wolves"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. to the slain: (O, TA:*) Abu-l-' Abbás says that the meaning is, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the hyena displays her teeth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"because the wolf contends with her over the slain: and some say that the poet means, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the hyena rejoices because of the slain."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b9-  One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaHikati","text_ar":"ضَحِكَتِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~amurapu","text_ar":"السَّمُرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"smrp","text_ar":"سمرة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gum-acacia-tree"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flowed with its gum:"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DHkt","text_ar":"ضحكت"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning “ she menstruated. ” (Bd in xi. 74.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","S","MA","O","Msb","K","KL","IDrd","Az","TK","MF","Skr","ISd","Kzw","Fr"]},{"entry_id":"n25595","headword_ar":"ضَحْكٌ","root":"DHk","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[originally an inf. n., a contraction of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaHikN","text_ar":"ضَحِكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"appearance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"appearing, of the central incisors"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the front teeth"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by reason of happiness, joy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gladness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  And hence, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wonder."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.)       -A2-  [As an epithet,] A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose teeth are white."},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, O, TA.)       -A3-  [And as a subst., properly so termed,]"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1772},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"White front teeth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, O, K.) ―         -b2-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Honey:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"white honey;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-Es-Seed, TA;) likened to the front teeth because of its intense whiteness: (AA, O, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honey in its comb;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ahodN","text_ar":"شَهْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b3-  And, (O, K,) some say, (O,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fresh butter."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K.) ―         -b4-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Snow."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K.) ―         -b5-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Blossoms,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flowers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"white blossoms"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flowers;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naworN","text_ar":"نَوْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O, and so in copies of the K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuwrN","text_ar":"نُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (So in a copy of the K.) ―         -b6-  And (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloE","text_ar":"طَلْع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spadix"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the palm-tree when its envelope bursts open from it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * O, * K;) in the dial. of Belhárith Ibn-Kaab: (O:) accord. to Th,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is in the interior of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloEap","text_ar":"طَلْعَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[here meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spathe of the palm-tree"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: as AA says, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waliyEap","text_ar":"وَلِيعَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waliyE","text_ar":"وَلِيع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[thus differently written in two different places in the TA,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloE","text_ar":"طَلْع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spathe of the palm-tree"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is eaten;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaH~aAkN","text_ar":"ضَحَّاكٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b7-  And (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"middle of a road;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) and so, accord. to the K, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaH~aAkN","text_ar":"ضَحَّاكٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but, correctly, this should have been there mentioned as syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaHokN","text_ar":"ضَحْكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense next preceding. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","K","AA","O"]}]}}